INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1160, 53, 'osc001160', 'osc1160', 'JZ Vintage 12', '+', 267, 141, '', 0, 0.000, 13250, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p><span style="font-size: small">Vintage 12</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">&nbsp;<br />\r\n主要特点<br />\r\nl 大振膜电容话筒<br />\r\nl GDC12极头<br />\r\nl A类分离电路<br />\r\nl 组件公差为1.5%<br />\r\nl 心形指向<br />\r\nl 5年质保<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n附件<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nl 自带手工木盒<br />\r\nl 自带可调旋转支架<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n技术参数<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n传感器类型&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 电容<br />\r\n振膜有效直径&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 25 mm<br />\r\n频响范围&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 20 Hz to 20 kHz<br />\r\n指向性&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 心形<br />\r\n输出阻抗&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 50欧姆<br />\r\n额定负载阻抗&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &gt;1000欧姆<br />\r\n建议负载阻抗&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 500欧姆<br />\r\n灵敏度&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 22 mV/Pa&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n信噪比&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 76 dB&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n信噪比（A计权）&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 87db-A<br />\r\n本底噪声&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 6 dB-A&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n最大声压级&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 134 dB&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n动态范围&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 128 dB&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n幻象供电电压&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; +48 V (+/-4 V)<br />\r\n电流&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1.5 mA<br />\r\n输出接口&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; XLR，镀金触点<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n录音应用<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nJZ话筒借鉴及保留了C12的顶级品质，并通过采用带有黄金点技术的GDC12极头以及用晶体管替代电子管，来为Vintage 12添加上他们独特的标志。Vintage 12依然延续了Vintage系列的相同设计：内防震系统、可调旋转支架以及双层网罩。V12尤其适合录制男女人声、木吉他、吉他音箱以及鼓的Overhead。</span></p>', 'images/201207/1342691034979355180.jpg', 'images/201207/1342691034382011086.jpg', 'images/201207/1342691034948427205.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1342691034, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1352751086, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1197, 121, 'osc001197', 'osc1197', 'Mercury 66 Mk. III  压限放大器', '+', 118, 144, '', 0, 0.000, 71940, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<h1>Mercury 66 Mk. III</h1>\r\n<h5>All Tube, All Transformer Mono (Stereo-Linkable) Studio Limiting Amplifier</h5>\r\n<p>The new Mercury 66 Studio Limiting Amplifier [Mk. III] is an &lsquo;All Tube - All Transformer&rsquo;, fully balanced, variable-bias limiter. Based on the most sought after product in this genre, the legendary Fairchild 660. This limiting amplifier is recognized essential tool for making great recordings. Many manufacturers have tried to copy the Fairchild circuit but have failed to capture the true sonic essence and presented a similar look and functionality but failed to capture the overall tone of the original. Until now.</p>\r\n<p>Mercury Recording Equipment has gone to great lengths to recreate the pride and passion of the past, both sonically and aesthetically, while offering the reliability of a modern build. The choices made in looks, layout, functionality, features and build quality all answer back to one question: How would &quot;they&quot; have done it today? So, the Mercury 66, like all Mercury products, has no ICs (chips), and is proudly hand built and assembled in the USA using no-compromise parts / components and has transformer balanced inputs and outputs. With the vintage style VU meter, large bakelite knobs and powder coated chassis / front panel, the Mercury 66 has a very distinctive 1950s aesthetic so that they look as good as they sound!</p>\r\n<p>Some might ask, &quot;Why recreate one of the most complicated pieces of recording equipment ever made?&quot; The answer is: the Mercury 66 Studio Limiting Amplifier is based on the classic Fairchild 660 limiting amplifier because we were inspired by the unique sound that only this circuit can deliver to your audio signal path. There is truly nothing else like it. The Mercury 66 has a massive, custom power supply transformer, a choke, 3 audio transformers, a control amp transformer and 8 tubes squeezed into a 3U chassis. All together the M66 weighs in at 38 pounds for a mono amplifier! Proudly, using parts that are available today, we have met all the original specifications, but most importantly, the Mercury 66 sounds like a Fairchild 660.</p>\r\n<p>Performance features include:</p>\r\n<p>&bull;Exceptional tone and musical focus<br />\r\n&bull;Absence of audible thumps, distortion or noise<br />\r\n&bull;Extremely fast attack time that can produce full limiting in 1/5000th of a second<br />\r\n&bull;Variable release time from .3 seconds to 25 seconds<br />\r\n&bull;Useful as a limiter or a compressor depending on the program material and control settings<br />\r\n&bull;Reliability and stability (All components operate well below their rated maximums)<br />\r\n&bull;All tube, fully balanced (push-pull) transformer coupled circuitry<br />\r\n&bull;Simple, easy to use controls.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury 66 Studio Limiting Amplifier uses a single push-pull stage of amplification which are transformer coupled input and output (XLRs) with no capacitors in the signal path, with a high control voltage. The result: the unit never produces any audible thumps, and has low distortion and noise under all conditions (either as a limiter or straight-through amplifier). The control amplifier is also fully balanced, transformer coupled in/out. The unit makes use of a very stable high current vacuum tube voltage regulator. It has ample and accessible input, threshold, attack, release time and metering controls allowing for convenience in the control room when making adjustments. The attack time is very fast and catches short transients. The release time of .3 to 25 seconds provides real flexibility: Three positions of the six available make the release time a function of program material, with fast recovery for short duration peaks and overall reduction of program level should the program level remain high. It can be used as a limiter or compressor. For example, use it as a 2 to 1 ratio compressor with a threshold 5 dB below average level, or as a peak limiter with a 20 to 1 ratio with threshold 10 dB above normal program level, or anywhere between these extremes.</p>\r\n<p>One notable change on the Mercury 66 is the addition of the DC Adjust Control. On an original Fairchild 660 this was called DC Threshold and was on the rear of the unit (not accessible from front panel). We put that control on the front panel and labeled it DC Adjust to not confuse the Threshold function. The DC Adjust lets you control DC (Direct Current) in part of the circuit to give the user more control of the functionality and level of compression. This gives you the control how the amplifier reacts to the audio signal and basically how hard the compression tube &lsquo;works&rsquo;, allowing you to &lsquo;smash&rsquo; the signal or just add a &lsquo;soft touch&rsquo; of compression along with the velvet tone and overwhelming musicality of the amplifier. This is possible by turning the DC Adjust to the far left (counter clockwise) on the M66 to add more DC and more compression [or saturation] &amp;mdhas; turn to the far right (clockwise) to decrease the amount of DC and the amount compression [or saturation, for a lack of a better term and to make things easier to understand]. The best thing about this feature is you can find that &lsquo;sweet spot&rsquo; for that perfect amount of compression. We like to think of this as the ''magic knob'' as do most of our users and this sets the Mercury 66 apart from the original and other compressors and limiting amplifiers available today.</p>\r\n<p>Front Panel Controls:</p>\r\n<p>&bull;Input Gain<br />\r\n&bull;AC Threshold<br />\r\n&bull;Attack/Release<br />\r\n&bull;DC Adjust<br />\r\n&bull;Meter Zero (Trim)<br />\r\n&bull;Stereo Link<br />\r\n&bull;Power on/off Switch</p>\r\n<p>Attack and Release Times:</p>\r\n<p>&bull;Position 1 - Attack [ Fast - 0.2 ] Release, in Seconds [ 0.3 ]<br />\r\n&bull;Position 2 - Attack [ Fast - 0.2 ] Release, in Seconds [ 0.8 ]<br />\r\n&bull;Position 3 - Attack [ Med. - 0.4 ] Release, in Seconds [ 2.0 ]<br />\r\n&bull;Position 4 - Attack [ Slow - 0.8 ] Release, in Seconds [ 5.0 ]<br />\r\n&bull;Position 5 - Attack [ Med. - 0.4 ] Release, in Seconds [ Auto: 2.0 peaks, 10.0 program ]<br />\r\n&bull;Position 6 - Attack [ Fast - 0.2 ] Release, in Seconds [ Auto: 0.3 peaks, 25.0 program ]</p>', 'images/201301/1359085542418620212.jpg', 'images/201301/1359085542301471340.jpg', 'images/201301/1359085542828266196.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1359085542, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1362091339, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1161, 53, 'osc001161', 'osc1161', 'JZ Vintage 11', '+', 311, 141, '', 0, 0.000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p><span style="font-size: small">Vintage 11</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">&nbsp;<br />\r\n主要特点<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nl 大振膜电容话筒<br />\r\nl GDC11极头<br />\r\nl A类分离电路<br />\r\nl 组件公差为1.5%<br />\r\nl 心形指向<br />\r\nl 5年质保<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n附件<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nl 自带手工木盒<br />\r\nl 自带可调旋转支架<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n技术参数<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n传感器类型&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 电容<br />\r\n振膜有效直径&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 27 mm<br />\r\n频响范围&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 20 Hz to 20 kHz<br />\r\n指向性&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 心形<br />\r\n输出阻抗&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 50欧姆<br />\r\n额定负载阻抗&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &gt;1000欧姆<br />\r\n建议负载阻抗&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 500欧姆<br />\r\n灵敏度&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 22 mV/Pa&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n信噪比&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 76.5 dB&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n信噪比（A计权）&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 87.5db-A <br />\r\n本底噪声&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 6.5 dB-A&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n最大声压级&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 134 dB&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n动态范围&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 128 dB&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n幻象供电电压&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; +48 V (+/-4 V)<br />\r\n电流&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;2 mA<br />\r\n输出接口&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; XLR，镀金触点<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n录音应用<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nV11是广受好评的Vintage系列话筒的一个转折点，它保留了Vintage系列的传统以及所有所有JZ话筒都具有的高品质，但它却并非那些传奇话筒如U47、U67及C12的翻版或改进，而是有着全新的话筒设计。数字11代表2011年，在这一年新的经典话筒诞生了。V11致力于让那些热爱高水准录音质量以及追求突破现有制作标准的人们得偿所愿。<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&ldquo;毫无疑问，V11值得尝试。事实上，比起同等价位的其他话筒，它肯定更能赢得许多追求音色个性的用户的喜爱。&rdquo;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &mdash; John Thornton, Resolution<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&ldquo;V11是一款用途广泛的话筒，音质也很棒。对我来说，V11中频提升平滑，声音染色少，噪音低，这些都是它出彩的地方。&rdquo;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &mdash;Paul White, Sound and Sound</span></p>', 'images/201207/1342750959894038419.jpg', 'images/201207/1342750959394432098.jpg', 'images/201207/1342750959577503193.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1342750959, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1343848174, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1198, 151, 'osc001198', 'osc1198', 'Mercury EQ-H1 Mk. III  单通道均衡器', '+', 98, 144, '', 0, 0.000, 20490, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<h1>EQ-H1 Mk. III</h1>\r\n<h5>Studio Program Equalizer</h5>\r\n<p>The Mercury EQ-H1 features a passive EQ circuit with a single ended gain make up amplifier topology, based on the vintage &lsquo;Pultec EQH&rsquo; circuit. The Mercury EQ-H1 circuit provides a musically satisfying result unobtainable with active and parametric EQs, since it does not rely upon negative feedback (and all its associated phase and dynamic distortions) to achieve equalization. The EQ-H1, like all Mercury products, has transformer balanced (XLR) input and outputs. The only modern additions or changes to the original are a much more powerful and stable power supply and running DC on the heaters, rather than AC, and two additional frequencies to expand the range and make it more flexible.</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury EQ-H1, EQ-P1, EQ-H2 and EQ-P2 are all based on the original Pultec equalizers which were tools developed to deal with the limitations of recorded music. Limitations that most often manifest themselves in the highest and lowest frequencies of the program material. The Mercury Studio Program Equalizers, like the family of original Pultec EQs, are originally designed to bring back the life and musicality lost in a recording. Whether by accident or genius, nothing has been able to do this better in music production than a passive equalizer with tube gain make up amplifier (&lsquo;Pultec style&rsquo;) equalizer. The interaction of the passive boosting and attenuating shelving EQs (not relying on negative feedback), as well as the transformers, tubes and other amplification circuitry all add to the incredibly musical character of the product. Working engineers try other types of equalizers, but always end up coming back to the Pultec style as the equalizer of choice for those final touches while tracking or mixing and even mastering at times.</p>\r\n<p>Now in this modern age of digital recording, where the source you put into the DAW is exactly what you have on the track, with no rounded edges, no slight compression and none of the &ldquo;pixie dust&rdquo; that came with analog tape, the Mercury family of equalizers are needed more than ever to help add the musicality, warmth and tone to your tracks that we have all treasured.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Frequencies</strong><br />\r\nLow Frequency Select (CPS; Cycles per second): 20, 30, 60, 100, 200 Hz <br />\r\nLow Frequency Boost Control: Shelf Boost, 0dB to +13dB <br />\r\nLow Frequency Attenuate Control: Shelf Atten. 0dB to -17dB <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Select (KCS; kilocycles per second ): 3, 4, 5, 8, 10, 12, 16 kHz <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Boost Control: Shelf Boost, 0dB to +16dB <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Attenuate Control: 10k Shelf Attenuate, 0dB to -16dB <br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'images/201301/1359085808172131442.jpg', 'images/201301/1359085808280845897.jpg', 'images/201301/1359085808633950541.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1359085808, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1363135717, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1162, 53, 'osc001162', 'osc1162', 'JZ BT201系列话筒(BT201|1，BT201|3 & BT201|3S)', '+', 159, 141, '', 0, 0.000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<div align="left">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">BT201 系列话筒(BT201|1，BT201|3 &amp; BT201|3S)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small"><br />\r\n主要特点<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nl 小振膜电容话筒<br />\r\nl 磁力可更换极头<br />\r\nl A类分离电路<br />\r\nl 组件公差为1.5%<br />\r\nl 心形、超心形指向<br />\r\nl 5年质保<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n附件<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nl 自带手工木盒<br />\r\nl 包含心形、超心形、超心形-20dB<br />\r\n三种话筒头（BT201|1只有心形）<br />\r\nl 可选全指向话筒头BT|O<br />\r\nl 可选防震架JZI|7<br />\r\nl 可选支撑托架JZ|HLDR<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n提示：BT201|3S 是一对经过配对的BT201|3<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n技术参数<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n传感器类型&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 电容<br />\r\n振膜有效直径&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 13 mm<br />\r\n频响范围&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 20 Hz to 20 kHz<br />\r\n指向性&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 心形、超心形<br />\r\n输出阻抗&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 50欧姆<br />\r\n额定负载阻抗&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &gt;1000欧姆<br />\r\n建议负载阻抗&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 250欧姆<br />\r\n灵敏度&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 11 mV/Pa<br />\r\n信噪比&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 71 dB<br />\r\n信噪比（A计权）&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 82db-A&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n本底噪声&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 12 dB-A&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n最大声压级&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 140 dB&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n动态范围&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 128 dB&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n幻象供电电压&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; +48 V (+/-4 V)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n电流&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2 mA&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n输出接口&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; XLR，镀金触点&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n录音应用<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nBT201系列话筒主要应用于原声吉他、打击乐以及鼓话筒，无论是作为Overhead使用还是作为鼓组任一部分的近距离拾音应用都可以胜任。最疯狂的录音师甚至用来录制人声，为作品带上独特的色彩。强烈建议使用BT201时搭配使用BH系列和BT301系列，无论在任何情况下都能得到极棒的音色，特别是原声吉他。</span></p>', 'images/201207/1342751139241545307.jpg', 'images/201207/1342751139400755873.jpg', 'images/201207/1342751139673843600.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1342751139, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1352751166, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1199, 151, 'osc001199', 'osc1199', 'Mercury EQ-P1 Mk. III  单通道均衡器', '+', 94, 144, '', 0, 0.000, 23740, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p>The Mercury EQ-H1, EQ-P1, EQ-H2 and EQ-P2 are all based on the original Pultec equalizers which were tools developed to deal with the limitations of recorded music. Limitations that most often manifest themselves in the highest and lowest frequencies of the program material. The Mercury Studio Program Equalizers, like the family of original Pultec EQs, are originally designed to bring back the life and musicality lost in a recording. Whether by accident or genius, nothing has been able to do this better in music production than a passive equalizer with tube gain make up amplifier (&lsquo;Pultec style&rsquo;) equalizer. The interaction of the passive boosting and attenuating shelving EQs (not relying on negative feedback), as well as the transformers, tubes and other amplification circuitry all add to the incredibly musical character of the product. Working engineers try other types of equalizers, but always end up coming back to the Pultec style as the equalizer of choice for those final touches while tracking or mixing and even mastering at times.</p>\r\n<p>Now in this modern age of digital recording, where the source you put into the DAW is exactly what you have on the track, with no rounded edges, no slight compression and none of the &ldquo;pixie dust&rdquo; that came with analog tape, the Mercury family of equalizers are needed more than ever to help add the musicality, warmth and tone to your tracks that we have all treasured.</p>\r\n<p>Frequencies<br />\r\nLow Frequency Select (CPS; Cycles per second): 20, 30, 60, 100, 200 Hz <br />\r\nLow Frequency Boost Control: Shelf Boost, 0dB to +13dB <br />\r\nLow Frequency Attenuate Control: Shelf Atten. 0dB to -17dB <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Select (KCS; kilocycles per second ): 3, 4, 5, 8, 10, 12, 16 kHz <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Boost Control: Shelf Boost, 0dB to +16dB <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Attenuate Control: 10k Shelf Attenuate, 0dB to -16dB</p>', 'images/201301/1359086044609861309.jpg', 'images/201301/1359086044892652529.jpg', 'images/201301/1359086044019357838.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1359086044, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1363135693, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1200, 120, 'osc001200', 'osc1200', 'Mercury Grand PreQ15s 通道条', '+', 99, 144, '', 0, 0.000, 23940, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<h1>Grand PreQ15s</h1>\r\n<h5>Discrete, Mono, Studio Microphone Amplifier with 3 Band Equalizer and High &amp; Low Pass Filters</h5>\r\n<!--p>Mercury Grand PreQ15s Studio Channel - The New, Alternative British Classic Studio Channel</p-->\r\n<p>The Mercury Grand PreQ15s is a fully discrete mono studio channel with 3-band equalizer, high &amp; low pass filters and fully balanced transformer coupled inputs and outputs. The GPQ15s has many additions to the classic circuit as well as all the modern features you will require packed into a solidly built 1U chassis. The Mercury GPQ15s boasts premium components, custom transformers, and is proudly built in the USA. The GPQ15s comes with an external premium quality power supply, the Mercury DC-1.</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury Grand PreQ15s (GPQ15s) Studio Channel contains the Mercury Grand Pre Microphone Amplifier, Line Input Amplifier, Response Selection, High and Low Frequency Filter Circuits and Output Level Control.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p>\r\n<p>Direct Mic/Line Switch:<br />\r\nWhen not engaged, the input XLR at the rear of the GPQ15s is the input source for either mic or line inputs. When the switch is engaged, the 1/4&quot; jack (below the switch) becomes the input source, accepting an instrument level signal (bass or guitar). This jack uses our Mercury FDI (Fet Direct Input) MKII circuit to convert to mic level and runs into the input transformer and complete GPQ15s circuits for the ability to have amazing control and tone on &lsquo;direct&rsquo; recordings.</p>\r\n<p>Direct Input (1/4&quot; Jack):<br />\r\nThis input is used when the Direct Mic/Line Switch is engaged for instrument level sources, giving you the ability to record guitar or bass directly.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Gain Control (Course Gain - Input Attenuator):<br />\r\n0dB and -12dB for line level sources, -24dB, -36dB, -48dB and -60dB for mic level sources.</p>\r\n<p>Fine Gain Control:<br />\r\nAt the 12 o&rsquo;clock position, the Fine Gain Control is at 0dB, and the amount of input gain is the same as shown on the Gain Control or Course Gain (to the left). Turning the Fine Gain Control counter-clockwise, you can reduce the amount of gain up to -8dB. Turning the Fine Gain Control clockwise, you can add up to +8dB of gain, in addition to the amount shown on the Gain Control or Course Gain.</p>\r\n<p>Output Level Control (Fader):<br />\r\nThe Output Level Control allows you to reduce the level of the output of the GPQ15s. This works like the fader on your console''s input channel. Turn the Output Level Control completely clockwise and the fader is &lsquo;open&rsquo;, allowing the maximum amount of output level. Turn the Output Level Control counter-clockwise to reduce the amount of output of the GPQ15s, all the way down to zero output level.</p>\r\n<p>Phantom ON/Off LED (Red) and Phantom On/Off Switch:<br />\r\nWhen engaged, Phantom Power (48V DC) is on and will power your phantom powered microphone.</p>\r\n<p>Phase ON/Off LED (White) and Phase On/Off Switch:<br />\r\nWhen not engaged, the phase is &lsquo;normal&rsquo; or Pin 2 hot. When engaged, the phase is &lsquo;reversed&rsquo; or Pin 3 hot.</p>\r\n<p>EQ In/Out LED (Blue) and EQ In/Out Switch:<br />\r\nWhen not engaged, the EQ Section (Treble, Presence and Bass) are &lsquo;out&rsquo;. When engaged, the EQ Section is &lsquo;In&rsquo;.</p>', 'images/201301/1359089569697242918.jpg', 'images/201301/1359089569472723059.jpg', 'images/201301/1359089569297159161.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1359089569, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1364327291, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1163, 53, 'osc001163', 'osc1163', 'JZ BT301', '+', 156, 141, '', 0, 0.000, 13290, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<div align="left">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">BT301</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small"><br />\r\n主要特点<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nl 中尺寸振膜电容话筒<br />\r\nl GDC3极头<br />\r\nl A类分离电路<br />\r\nl 组件公差为0.4%<br />\r\nl 心形指向<br />\r\nl 终身质保<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n附件<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nl 自带手工木盒<br />\r\nl 可选防震架JZI|7<br />\r\nl 可选支撑托架JZ|HLDR<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n技术参数<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n传感器类型&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 电容<br />\r\n振膜有效直径&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 21 mm<br />\r\n频响范围&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 20 Hz to 20 kHz<br />\r\n指向性&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 心形<br />\r\n输出阻抗&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 50欧姆<br />\r\n额定负载阻抗&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &gt;1000欧姆<br />\r\n建议负载阻抗&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 500欧姆<br />\r\n灵敏度&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 33 mV/Pa<br />\r\n信噪比&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 76 dB<br />\r\n信噪比（A计权）&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 87db-A<br />\r\n本底噪声&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5.5dB-A <br />\r\n最大声压级&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 133.5 dB<br />\r\n动态范围&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 128 dB&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n幻象供电电压&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; +48 V (+/-4 V)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n电流&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2 mA&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n输出接口&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; XLR，镀金触点<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp; <br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n录音应用<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nJZ BT301是一款能完美胜任录制重要原声乐器的话筒。GDC3振膜能清晰有效的捕捉弓弦及拨弦乐器，并将其自然的放大。巧妙的造型能将后方轴向上对心形指向响应的干扰降到最低。BT301是录制以下乐器的理想选择：扫弦乐器、立式钢琴、大提琴、低音提琴、手鼓等。它在任何高端话筒队列中都有一席之地。</span></p>', 'images/201207/1342751479752077256.jpg', 'images/201207/1342751479100140029.jpg', 'images/201207/1342751479663137530.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1342751479, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1352751191, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1201, 120, 'osc001201', 'osc1201', 'Mercury MSC-72 通道条', '+', 64, 144, '', 0, 0.000, 37490, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<h1>Mercury Studio Channel 72 (MSC-72)</h1>\r\n<h5>M72s Studio Microphone Amplifier with EQ-H1 Studio Program Equalizer</h5>\r\n<p><strong>The MSC-72 Mic Amp</strong></p>\r\n<p>The M72s is based on the most sought after vintage &quot;V series&quot; module, the &lsquo;Telefunken/Siemens V72s,&rsquo; which is most famous for being used in REDD.37 consoles used on the early Beatles recordings by George Martin at Abbey Road Studios in London, England.</p>\r\n<p>Unlike those vintage modules that had a fixed 34dB gain, The gain of the Mercury M72s is variable from 28dB to 58dB, in 3dB increments. Also, there is an option of a selectable Input Pad of -16dB or -28dB for even more control. When the -28dB pad is engaged and it is set at the lowest gain setting (28dB) you can run line level signal through the M72s to add warmth and tonality to any tracks, mixes, keyboards, drum machines, samples etc... There are also all the modern features we expect on a new piece of equipment: Phantom Power (on/off) , Phase (Polarity) Reversal, and our amazing sounding F.D.I. (FET Direct Input) Circuit.</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury FDI (FET Direct Input), a proprietary J-Fet circuit, based on a class-A tube topology. The Mercury FDI is designed to reproduce every nuance of a direct recording, while the circuit lets the tube or solid-state character of the amplifier determine the overall tone. The instrument DI signal is sent through the entire microphone preamp circuitry, including Mercury&rsquo;s custom, massive input transformers, so that the individual character of each preamp comes through.</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury M72s has the rich lows and punchy mids giving you a instant vocal tone, or assisting with a realistic acoustic guitar tone, punch to bass guitar. The same reaction to instruments or source as the vintage module but with slightly more open high end and openness. The Mercury M72s Studio Microphone Amplifier has that &quot;vintage&quot; tone and &quot;break up&quot; like the original circuit but it is a bit more musical over all (not cleaner, more musical, there is a huge difference).</p>\r\n<p>Tubes: The Mercury M72s amplifier in the Mercury Studio Channel 72 uses two EF806s tubes.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The MSC-72 EQ</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Mercury EQ-H1 features a passive EQ circuit with a single ended gain make up amplifier topology, based on the vintage &lsquo;Pultec EQH&rsquo; circuit. The Mercury EQH2 circuit provides a musically satisfying result unobtainable with active and parametric EQs, since the EQH2 does not rely upon negative feed back (and all it''s associated phase and dynamic distortions) to achieve equalization. The EQH2, like all Mercury products, has transformer balanced (XLR) input and outputs. The only additions or changes to the original are a much more powerful and stable power supply and running DC on the heaters, rather than AC.</p>\r\n<p>EQH2 vs EQP2: Simply, the key to the tone of these two circuits is it&rsquo;s amplifier, and Mercury EQ-H2 and EQ-P2 have different amplifiers to make up the gain lost by the passive equalizer circuit, thus it has a different tone. Meaning the EQH2 and EQP2 sound different on the same application, and have a different reaction to the same instrumentation or voice. The EQH2, like the mono version EQ-H1, is more punchy and robust and has a slight push in the low end and lower midrange. The EQP2, like the mono version EQ-P1, is more open and silky, and equally adds warm to highs, mids and lows of your source. Although both sound amazing on any application and are both multi-purpose tools (equalizers) in the studio, if you had both you could then choose between applications. The Mercury EQH2 is warm and fluid but a bit &quot;thicker&quot; than the EQP2, thus shines on thickening (and pushing forward in the mix) your Vocals, Bass, Kick, Snare, and Acoustic Guitar etc... The Mercury EQP2 is great for Shaping and adding &lsquo;air&rsquo; to your vocals, Acoustic instruments, Guitar, Piano etc... and is magical strapped across your two buss to add musicality to you mix.</p>\r\n<p>Tubes: The Mercury EQ-H1 amplifier uses a 1x 12AX7 and 1x 12BH7, per channel.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Frequencies: </strong></p>\r\n<p>Low Frequency Select (CPS; Cycles per second): 20, 30, 60, 100, 200 Hz <br />\r\nLow Frequency Boost Control: Shelf Boost, 0dB to +13dB <br />\r\nLow Frequency Attenuate Control: Shelf Atten. 0dB to -17dB <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Select (KCS; kilocycles per second ): 3, 4, 5, 8, 10, 12, 16 kHz <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Boost Control: Shelf Boost, 0dB to +16dB <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Attenuate Control: 10k Shelf Attenuate, 0dB to -16dB</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury EQ-H1 and EQ-P1 are based on the original Pultec equalizers which were tools developed to deal with the limitations of recorded music. Limitations that most often manifest themselves in the highest and lowest frequencies of the program material. The family of Pultec EQs were originally designed to bring back the life and musicality lost in the recording. Whether by accident or genius, nothing has been able to do it better. The interaction of the passive boosting and attenuating shelving EQs (not relying on negative feed back), as well as the transformers, tubes and other amplification circuitry all add to the incredibly musical character of the product. Working engineers try other types of equalizers, but always end up coming back to the Pultec style as the equalizer of choice for those final touches while tracking or mixing and even mastering.</p>', 'images/201301/1359090274772801007.jpg', 'images/201301/1359090274103394252.jpg', 'images/201301/1359090274596751198.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1359090274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1364327186, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1164, 180, 'osc001164', 'osc1164', 'JZ Michael Wagener Kit 套装', '+', 125, 141, '', 0, 0.000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<div align="left">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">Michael Wagener Kit 套装</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">Michael Wagener Kit套装包含一支 BT-201小振膜心形电容话筒和一支限量版的BT-301中振膜电容话筒。这个组合是由传奇录音师Michael Wagener（Metallica、 Ozzy OsbourneAlice Cooper...）发明的，用来给鼓的Overhead以及木吉他拾音。<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nMichael Wagener 评价 BT201/BT301 组合：<br />\r\n&ldquo;BT301是我录制节奏钹必用的话筒，录踩镲时则大量使用BT201。&rdquo;</span></p>', 'images/201207/1342752102003504106.jpg', 'images/201207/1342752102348432509.jpg', 'images/201207/1342752102668892267.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1342751997, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1343847493, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1165, 180, 'osc001165', 'osc1165', 'JZ DMK1 鼓话筒套装', '+', 119, 141, '', 0, 0.000, 12990, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p><span style="font-size: small">DMK1</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">&nbsp;<br />\r\nJZ DMK1鼓话筒套装最常见的用途就是在录音室或现场拾取鼓的Overhead和底鼓。JZ DMK1包含三支BT-201小振膜电容话筒，其中两支心形的BT201是经过配对的，剩下的一支BT201带有-20dB衰减功能，用来录制底鼓。套装中还包含3个话筒夹和一个坚固的手提箱，方便携带并且安全可靠。<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n关于电路部分<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nJZ话筒采用现代A类分离电路设计。每个部件都由手工筛选、测试及组装以达到最佳性能，并确保有最干净的信号路径及尽可能低的低噪。<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n工艺及质量<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nl 手工筛选及测试组件<br />\r\nl 所选组件公差不超过1.5 %<br />\r\nl BH1S 和BT301系列话筒公差为0.4 %<br />\r\nl 手工焊接组件<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n电路设计<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nl A类分离电路<br />\r\nl 少用电子管<br />\r\nl 少用变压器<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;Vintage系列电路<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nBH1S 系列话筒的PAD开关<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nl BH1S话筒：-10和-20dB<br />\r\nl 对频响曲线的影响极其微小<br />\r\n包含PAD开关的JZ话筒可降低信号电平5dB到20dB。JZ话筒的PAD开关设计在振膜之后，以避免改变高频及低频。它只是降低了输入信号电平以确保振膜在不改变频率响应特性的前提下应对高声压级。</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">&ldquo;对我而言，JZ话筒轻松胜出。AKG 460s声音很棒，但是在混音中需要调节EQ。而且和BT-201s相比，录鼓时声音有点闷。无需多言！抱歉了 460s，我甚至忘了拍张照片！&rdquo;&nbsp;&nbsp; &mdash;Jon Mattox</span></p>', 'images/201207/1342752325531950535.jpg', 'images/201207/1342752325099504611.jpg', 'images/201207/1342752325634205263.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1342752325, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1352751424, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1202, 120, 'osc001202', 'osc1202', 'Mercury MSC-76 通道条', '+', 63, 144, '', 0, 0.000, 44940, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<h1>Mercury Studio Channel 76 (MSC-76)</h1>\r\n<h5>M76m Studio Microphone Amplifier with EQ-P1 Studio Program Equalizer</h5>\r\n<p>New from the Mercury Custom Shop is Mercury&rsquo;s twist on the professional studio channel, the Mercury Studio Channel 76. The MSC-76 is two independent channels of a Mercury M76m Studio Microphone Amplifier and a Mercury EQ-P1 Program Equalizer. Both amplifiers (the microphone amplifier and EQ&rsquo;s gain make up amplifier) are fully transformer balanced, with the option to use them together or independently with separate XLR inputs and outputs on the rear of chassis. The MSC-76 is simply two great Mercury products in one 3U chassis.</p>\r\n<p>Looking at other choices of &ldquo;combo boxes,&rdquo; especially ones with compressors along with pre-amps and EQs, choosing to cut corners to either be able to save costs, which usually means less transformers, and or to save space to be able to fit all the components in the products chassis, we wanted to do something much different. Unlike many &ldquo;channel strips&rdquo; or &ldquo;combo boxes&rdquo; in the marketplace, no corners were cut in the Mercury Studio Channel 76 (or our other Studio Channel &ndash; the Mercury Studio Channel 72).</p>\r\n<p>With the philosophy that each part of your signal chain is important, after selecting a microphone for a specific source, the foundation starts with your microphone amplifier. We designed our Mercury Studio Channels to be an obvious choice to follow any microphone in your signal chain by matching up our tube Mercury Studio Microphone Amplifiers with our tube Studio Program Equalizers. We did not consider a compressor or limiter to be part of the product from the very beginning, thinking just like a microphone, the compressor is going to vary much more often depending on application or source you are recording concentrated on the heart of the signal chain. This would allow you to use it with any microphone you have in your mic locker and any compressor in your rack, making a Mercury Studio Channel an obvious choice for engineers and producers who are looking for tone, warmth and musicality.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The MSC-76 Mic Amp</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury M76m Studio Microphone Amplifier is a recreation of the original German designed Telefunken/Siemens amplifier module used in many European broadcast and recording desks in the 1960s. However, the V76 modules are known as an outboard rack mounted mic pre-amp and are highly sought after by studios and engineers all over the world.</p>\r\n<p>Drawing on years of experience, repairing, rebuilding, and most importantly listening to the Telefunken/Siemens V76 modules it was our first priority to build a modern Studio Microphone Amplifier that sounds identical to the original. Mercury Recording Equipment Co. kept the integrity of the original circuit, the M76m has the same open, warm tonality created with the transformer balanced, dual stage, high gain amplifier, and uses four transformers and four tube per channel. Mercury has built what is quite possibly the ultimate combination of vintage sound and modern features to be the benchmark in a modern tube microphone amplifier.</p>\r\n<p>Tubes: The Mercury M76m amplifier in the Mercury Studio Channel 76 uses three EF806s tubes and one E83F tube.</p>\r\n<p>The MSC-76 Mic Amp Features &amp; Controls<br />\r\nThe Mercury M76m has Gain Control of 0 to +60dB in 6dB increments, that works in conjunction with the Level control and Output Attenuation. The Level Control, which will work as a fader, increasing (clockwise) and decreasing (counter clockwise) the amount of gain from the first stage to the second stage of the amplifier. This also allows you the ability to add musical &ldquo;fuzz&rdquo; by turning down your level (control) and adding more (coarse) gain. The Output Attenuation Control (-0 to -10dB) has been added for even more control, including the ability shape tones in several different ways, if desired. Unlike the original, we have added an Impedance Select Switch for both high and low impedance devices, as well as all the staple features one expects from a modern piece of equipment were added. Phantom Power (on/off) , Phase (Polarity) Reversal, and our amazing sounding FDI (FET Direct Input) Circuit.</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury FDI (FET Direct Input) is a proprietary J-Fet circuit, based on a class-A tube topology. The Mercury FDI is designed to reproduce every nuance of a direct recording, while the circuit lets the tube or solid-state character of the amplifier determine the overall tone. The instrument DI signal is sent through the entire microphone preamp circuitry, including Mercury&rsquo;s custom, massive input transformers, so that the individual character of each preamp comes through.</p>\r\n<p><img alt="" width="800" height="235" src="/images/upload/Image/mercury_msc76_back_big.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>The MSC-76 EQ</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury EQ-P1 is based on the vintage &lsquo;Pultec EQP1a&rsquo; circuit, which uses a passive EQ circuit with a fully balanced (push-pull) gain make up amplifier. This new Mercury production utilizes only the highest quality passive components, while remaining true to the original, and like all Mercury products, has transformer balanced input and outputs.</p>\r\n<p>Besides a much more powerful and stable power supply and running DC on the heaters, rather than AC, the only other modernization is one of Mercury EQP2&rsquo;s most popular features: the Mercury I.S.T. Switch.</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury I.S.T. Switch offers the choice to switch the Interstage Transformer in or out of the circuit. Giving engineers a choice with a flick of a switch between the standard Mercury warm, musical, &ldquo;vintage&rdquo; tone with the I.S.T. Switch not engaged (out) or a much more open and airy version of the same full, warm tone with the switch engaged (in). In the original Pultec EQP the Interstage transformer was always in the signal path. With the I.S.T. Switch engaged and the interstage transformer not in the circuit, there is slight widening of the sound and slightly more open top end. Many of today''s engineers value this feature on the Mercury EQ-P1 and now the Mercury EQP2 Studio Program Equalizers to have choice between two great, but different sounds without changing their frequencies or setting and hearing the change instantly. Note: With the I.S.T. Switch engaged or not, the input and output transformers are always in the circuit.</p>\r\n<p>Tubes: The Mercury EQ-P1 amplifier in the Mercury Studio Channel 76 uses one 12AX7 tube and one 12AU7 tube.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Frequencies: </strong></p>\r\n<p>Low Frequency Select (CPS; Cycles per second): 20, 30, 60, 100, 200 Hz <br />\r\nLow Frequency Boost Control: Shelf Boost, 0dB to +13dB <br />\r\nLow Frequency Attenuate Control: Shelf Atten. 0dB to -17dB <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Bandwidth Control: Sharp to Broad <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Select (KCS): 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8, 10, 12, 16k <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Boost Control: Shelf Boost, 0dB to +18dB <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Shelf Attenuate Select: 5, 10, &amp; 20k <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Attenuate Control: Shelf Attenuate, 0dB to +16dB</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury EQ-H1 and EQ-P1 are based on the original Pultec equalizers which were tools developed to deal with the limitations of recorded music. Limitations that most often manifest themselves in the highest and lowest frequencies of the program material. The family of Pultec EQs were originally designed to bring back the life and musicality lost in the recording. Whether by accident or genius, nothing has been able to do it better. The interaction of the passive boosting and attenuating shelving EQs (not relying on negative feed back), as well as the transformers, tubes and other amplification circuitry all add to the incredibly musical character of the product. Working engineers try other types of equalizers, but always end up coming back to the Pultec style as the equalizer of choice for those final touches while tracking or mixing and even mastering.<strong><br />\r\n</strong></p>', 'images/201301/1359090748916018115.jpg', 'images/201301/1359090748921691879.jpg', 'images/201301/1359090748030767390.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1359090748, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1364327162, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1166, 181, 'osc001166', 'osc1166', 'JZ BH|SPK', '+', 127, 141, '', 0, 0.000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<div style="text-align: left; text-indent: -21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt 21pt" align="left">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">BH|SPK</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">&nbsp;<br />\r\nl BH|SPK是为黑洞系列话筒特制的防震架与防喷罩套装（BH1S、BH1、 BH2和BH3）<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nl 防喷罩具有特殊的三维形状和表面结构。这种独特的形状有助于削弱呼吸的力度来减少爆破音。<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nl BH|SPK的造型十分紧凑以避免使用大型蜘蛛型防震架时所带来的不必要的反射。</span></p>', 'images/201207/1342753271836434122.jpg', 'images/201207/1342753271057978571.jpg', 'images/201207/1342753271723843208.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1342753271, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1343847574, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1167, 181, 'osc001167', 'osc1167', 'JZ PF', '+', 119, 141, '', 0, 0.000, 950, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p><span style="font-size: small"><br />\r\nJZ|PF<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nl JZ|PF是适用于所有话筒的通用型防喷罩。<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nl JZ|PF独特的工业设计最大程度的保证频率不受影响。紧凑的造型和独特的网格设计能减少不必要的反射，并比市场上同价位的防喷罩更有效的去除喷麦声。<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nl JZ|PF有45厘米长的鹅颈，方便摆放在任何位置。符合人体工程学的附件能轻松快速的固定在话筒支架上。</span></p>', 'images/201207/1342753384634013879.jpg', 'images/201207/1342753384539746745.jpg', 'images/201207/1342753384125994308.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1342753384, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1352751323, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1168, 181, 'osc001168', 'osc1168', 'JZI|7', '+', 116, 141, '', 0, 0.000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p><span style="font-size: small">&nbsp;JZI|7 </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">l JZI|7是适用于BT201和BT301系列话筒的可选防震架。其独特的复合材料结构带来极端有效的减震特性。</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">l JZI|7防震架是由Rycote按照JZ话筒指定的规格制作的。</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">l JZ强烈建议所有和BT201和BT301系列话筒尺寸类似（24mm）的笔形话筒使用JZI|7防震架。</span></p>', 'images/201207/1342753496404529862.jpg', 'images/201207/1342753496135696411.jpg', 'images/201207/1342753496746827988.png', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1342753496, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1343846593, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1169, 49, 'osc001169', 'osc1169', 'ADAM F7有源监听音箱', '+', 671, 34, '', 0, 0.000, 6800, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p><span style="font-size: small">F7音箱</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">F7具有与A7X相近的尺寸和音质，而价格却更低。<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n高音单元<br />\r\nF7也使用了ADAM Audio享有盛名的带状加速技术（ART技术），这一点就确保了F7同样具有清晰的音质。<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n低音单元<br />\r\n7寸碳布/纸复合纸盆与37mm的音圈搭配。它将完美的与ART单元相结合。F7具有深沉的低频下限，以及富有乐感的中频。<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n控制<br />\r\nF7与F5 使用了同样的控制模块： 1个音量旋钮（-&infin;到+6 dB）、2个房间EQ高频（&gt;5kHz）、低频（&lt;300Hz）。<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n技术指标：<br />\r\n&bull; 新的ART单元<br />\r\n&bull; 7寸碳布/纸复合纸盆低音单元<br />\r\n&bull; 高音单元：40W（rms）A/B功放<br />\r\n&bull; 低音单元：60W（rms）A/B功放<br />\r\n&bull;自动待机<br />\r\n&bull; 后面板有音量控制以及2个搁架均衡<br />\r\n&bull; 44Hz - 50kHz<br />\r\n&bull; XLR复合大三芯接口+RCA接口<br />\r\n&bull; 每对音箱最大声压级113dB<br />\r\n&bull; H x W x D: 321 x 225 x 266 mm<br />\r\n&bull; 9 kg<br />\r\n&bull; 质保2年</span></p>', 'images/201207/1343269735391897665.jpg', 'images/201207/1343269734716184287.jpg', 'images/201207/1343269734617390027.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1343269735, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1343850215, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1174, 53, 'osc001174', 'osc1174', 'DPA 4090 全指向高灵敏度电容话筒', '+', 141, 124, '', 0, 0.000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p>DPA 4090是一款高质量全指向性电容话筒。由于它自然真实而又开阔的音质，4090特别适用于录音棚或现场的录音。<br />\r\n134dB的声压级处理意味着它能够用于拾取任何乐器的声音如：吉他、弦乐器、钢琴或管乐器等。它的频率响应范围是20 Hz到20 kHz，4090能够拾取乐器所发出的全部声音。<br />\r\n设计精巧的漫反射话筒帽直径仅为5.4毫米，这是4090的一大特色。</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n技术指标：</p>\r\n<p>工作原理：压力式<br />\r\n拾音头类型: 预极化电容<br />\r\n电源供电：48V幻象电源<br />\r\n频率范围： &plusmn; 2 dB:<br />\r\n20 Hz - 20 kHz <br />\r\n方向特性：全指向性<br />\r\nA计权等价噪声级：23 dB(A) 每 20 ?Pa (最大26 dB(A))<br />\r\nITU-R BS.468-4等价噪声计：38 dB (最大40 dB)<br />\r\n拾音头直径：5.4mm<br />\r\n总谐波失真(THD)：&lt;1% THD达到123 dB声压级峰值<br />\r\n输出阻抗：&lt;40欧姆<br />\r\n线缆驱动能力：达到300m (984 ft)<br />\r\n最大声压级, 削波之前的峰值：134 dB<br />\r\n连接器输出：&lt;40欧姆<br />\r\n动态范围：100dB<br />\r\n信噪比, 在1Pa的1Kz(94 dB 声压级)：71 dB（A）<br />\r\n连接器：3针卡侬（标准的P48）<br />\r\n标称灵敏度，&plusmn;3 dB：20mV/Pa； -34 dB 每1 V/Pa<br />\r\n电流消耗：1.0Ma<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'images/201208/1346011791944224839.jpg', 'images/201208/1346011791544411076.jpg', 'images/201208/1346011791905682480.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1346011791, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1346011791, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1175, 104, 'osc001175', 'osc1175', 'Apogee Quartet 四重奏顶级音频接口', '+', 624, 41, '', 0, 0.000, 12950, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p><img alt="" width="400" height="296" src="/images/upload/Image/quartet_0_1346768886.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p>4进8出的USB 2音频接口，使用了顶级的AD/DA、话放、24bit/192kHz、ADAT/SMUX，美国制造。</p>\r\n<p>Quartet是Apogee专为Mac用户设计的4进8出音频接口，通过USB 2.0与苹果电脑连接，24bit/192kHz精度，前部有多达9个触摸点进行触控操作，超大的铝质旋钮可对音量进行精确的控制。</p>\r\n<p><img alt="" width="400" height="147" src="/images/upload/Image/quartet3_2_1346768886.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p><img alt="" width="400" height="146" src="/images/upload/Image/quartet4_3_1346768886.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Quartet主要特性：<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>4进8出USB 2.0音频接口</li>\r\n    <li>使用了Apogee最棒的AD/DA，24bit/192kHz精度</li>\r\n    <li>4个模拟输入使用最棒的话放</li>\r\n    <li>最多可连接3对监听音箱</li>\r\n    <li>带ADAT/SMUX数字输入接口</li>\r\n    <li>带MIDI输入接口</li>\r\n    <li>8个模拟输出接口包括6个平衡输出（+20dBu）和1个大两芯耳机输出</li>\r\n    <li>2个区域的OLED显示部分</li>\r\n    <li>超大的铝质旋钮可对音量进行精确的控制</li>\r\n    <li>6个触控点可选择输入和输出信号源</li>\r\n    <li>还有3个可分配功能的触控点</li>\r\n    <li>支持CoreAudio驱动，只能连接Mac电脑使用</li>\r\n    <li>美国制造！</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><img alt="" width="400" height="217" src="/images/upload/Image/quartet2_1_1346768886.jpg" /></p>', 'images/201210/1350241553651936169.jpg', 'images/201210/1350241553716101647.jpg', 'images/201210/1350241553229865296.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1350241553, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1350416544, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1176, 113, 'osc001176', 'osc1176', 'SPL Preference Preamplifiers双通道话筒放', '+', 155, 107, '', 0, 0.000, 9150, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>SPL公司最新研发的SPL Preference Preamplifiers双通道话筒放大器及SPL Preference &amp; TwinTube话放及电子管处理器还未上市已备受关注，众多音乐人更是在纷纷数次的电话咨询中翘首期盼。千呼万唤中他们终于向我们始来，神秘面纱将被揭开。</p>\r\n<p>SPL Preference Preamplifiers双通道话筒放大器特点：<br />\r\n最高可提供+72dB增益<br />\r\nVU表可反映平均电平及峰值电平<br />\r\n稳定的48V幻象电源供电<br />\r\n相位反转切换开关及高通滤波器</p>', 'images/201210/1351220888345555828.jpg', 'images/201210/1351220888053701308.jpg', 'images/201210/1351220888953208427.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1351220888, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1351220888, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1177, 113, 'osc001177', 'osc1177', 'SPL Preference & TwinTube话放及电子管处理器', '+', 209, 107, '', 0, 0.000, 10950, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p>SPL公司最新研发的SPL Preference Preamplifiers双通道话筒放大器及SPL Preference &amp; TwinTube话放及电子管处理器还未上市已备受关注，众多音乐人更是在纷纷数次的电话咨询中翘首期盼。千呼万唤中他们终于向我们始来，神秘面纱将被揭开。</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nTwinTube话放及电子管处理器特点：<br />\r\nTwinTube 的饱和效果可媲美磁带饱和效果的音质<br />\r\nSATURATION能带来更多温暖度和响度，以及微妙的清晰效果<br />\r\nHARMONICS可增加临场感及清晰度，且不会像EQ等效果般明显增加电平<br />\r\n可使信号在混音中更加靠前<br />\r\n用途广泛，适合各种信号：人声、原声吉他、鼓、弦乐、铜号等<br />\r\nPhonitor不但提供了标准的监听功能，还提供象如串扰（Crossfeed），音箱角度（ Speaker Angle）及中间电平（Center Level）等全新的控制参数。这些参数用来真实再现真实音箱声场中的宽度、平衡及总体氛围，让我们感到声音确实是从音箱里发出来的。串扰（Crossfeed）模拟出两个声道之间的信号差异，音箱角度（ Speaker Angle）决定了立体声场的宽度，中间电平（Center Level）用来调节左右声道的电平，获得理想的中间位置。</p>', 'images/201210/1351221373988330206.jpg', 'images/201210/1351221373855524531.jpg', 'images/201210/1351221373040133727.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1351221300, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1351221373, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1173, 49, 'osc001173', 'osc1173', 'GENELEC 6010AZM', '+', 234, 64, '', 0, 0.000, 8650, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p><span style="font-size: small">Genelec6010AZM是6010系列中带有光面铝色外观的一款外形独特的音箱。</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">新型真力6010A音箱是一个极具紧凑型特点的双分频有源音箱，它专为电脑音箱系统和其他近距离的倾听环境量身设计。精致小巧的外观设计、让人荡气回肠的音响效果和坚固耐用的构造是出行在外的发烧友随时享受完美倾听环境的理想选择。众多方面的创新、突破常规的设计风格让6010A在空间有限的应用环境里超越同侪，独树一帜。</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">出自真力研发团队与国际知名的芬兰设计师Harri Koskinen之手，6010A有源音箱内置了功率放大器、有源分音过滤器和自动保护电路。可通过RCA线性电平音频连接插头实现与电脑声卡、便携式MP3播放器或前置放大器的便捷连接。</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">铸铝的最低衍射箱体（MDE&trade;）和先进的指向性控制波导技术&trade;（DCW&trade;）实现了与先进的功放、电子电路以及最先进的分频器的完美匹配。虽然低音响应延伸到73 Hz （-3 dB），但由于采用了独特的新式后方衍射端口设计，音箱失真率极低。</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">独特的指向性特点、精确的音场定位、小巧紧凑的外观、灵活的安装选择让6010A音箱系统可以出色地满足各种监听需求。</span></p>', 'images/201208/1343946541300500332.jpg', 'images/201208/1343946541231529444.jpg', 'images/201208/1343946541786083184.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1343946541, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1349651605, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1170, 53, 'osc001170', 'osc1170', 'DPA 4006A电容话筒', '+', 381, 124, '', 0, 0.000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p><span style="font-size: small">这个型号的麦克风具有出色的灵敏度表现，平直的频率响应以及非常低的噪声。麦克风头选择德国银作材料，内置直径为16毫米的振膜。麦克风头在制作过程中经过了老化处理和强度测试，有很好的稳定性，可以应付很恶劣的环境条件，使用寿命也因此得到延长。4006对语言中的爆破声不敏感，也不会表现近距效应，既可用以近距离录人声，弦乐，木管乐器或弹拨乐器，也可以用来作A-B立体声录音。4006的标准配置中包括两只麦克风罩，即银色的DD0251近距离拾音麦克风罩和黑色的DD0297远距离拾音麦克风罩。</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small"><br />\r\n技术参数:<br />\r\n噪声级：5dB(A)<br />\r\n指向性：无方向<br />\r\n最大声压级：154dB<br />\r\n标称灵敏度：40/10mV/Pa<br />\r\n供电方式：130V/p48<br />\r\n频率响应：10Hz/20kHz-20kHz&plusmn;2dB </span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'images/201207/1343272447970834974.jpg', 'images/201207/1343272447362074840.jpg', 'images/201207/1343272447102429740.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1343272447, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1345751993, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1171, 49, 'osc001171', 'osc1171', 'ADAM F5有源监听音箱', '+', 240, 0, '', 0, 0.000, 5000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p><span style="font-size: small">F5音箱</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">F5是F系列音箱中体积较小的一款，适用于小型监听环境的监听音箱。<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n高音单元<br />\r\nF系列使用了ADAM著名的ART高音单元技术的最新版本。它的单元比X-ART高音单元稍小一点，也是高音单元进一步发展的趋势。（详见第7页以获得<br />\r\n更多信息。）<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n中低音单元<br />\r\n正如其名，F5使用了1个5寸中低音单元，包括碳布/纸复合纸盆以及1个25mm音圈。尽管这个低音单元尺寸以及箱体大小有限，F5仍然可以重现令人惊异的中低频声音。<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n控制<br />\r\nF5的后面板上有多个可调整参数，以适应各种不同的环境：2个房间EQ，高频（&gt;5kHz）、<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n低频<br />\r\n（&lt;300Hz），以及音量控制旋钮（-&infin;到+6 dB）。<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n技术指标：<br />\r\n&bull;新的ART高音单元<br />\r\n&bull; 5寸碳布/纸复合纸盆中低音单元<br />\r\n&bull; 2个25W（rms）A/B功放<br />\r\n&bull;自动待机<br />\r\n&bull;后面板有音量控制以及2个搁架均衡<br />\r\n&bull; 52Hz - 50kHz<br />\r\n&bull; XLR复合大三芯接口+RCA接口<br />\r\n&bull;每对音箱最大声压级110dB<br />\r\n&bull; H x W x D: 290 x 185 x 230 mm<br />\r\n&bull; 6.8 kg<br />\r\n&bull;质保2年</span></p>', 'images/201207/1343286595818958027.jpg', 'images/201207/1343286594453862585.jpg', 'images/201207/1343286594827400689.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1343286595, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1343850073, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1178, 121, 'osc001178', 'osc1178', 'Crane Song TRAKKER单通道压缩器', '+', 130, 143, '', 0, 0.000, 26775, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p>TRAKKER是一款采用离散式A类电路设计的高品质压缩限制器，可作为解决录音、广播及现场扩声等专业应用场合实际问题的多功能工具，最大限度地发挥并改善现有的声音。它具备可调节的阈值、起始时间、释放时间、拐点形状及增益提升旋钮，带有过载指示灯的22段VU表能够显示电平压缩量，并精确地监听输出电平大小。</p>\r\n<p>除了这些常见压缩限制器调整参数外，TRAKKER还具备一项特殊的调整内容&mdash;&mdash;包括Hard、Soft、Optical及AirOptical在内的四种可选音色特性处理，而其中每一种又涵盖四种不同的放大器/增益控制设置，具体如下：</p>\r\n<p>-CLEAN（干净透明声音）</p>\r\n<p>-VINTAGE（复古电子管或老式A类单元声音）</p>\r\n<p>-C-VCA（带有VCA模拟的干净透明声音）</p>\r\n<p>-V-VCA（带有VCA模拟的复古单元声音）</p>\r\n<p>此外，TRAKKER支持8台关联以进行环绕声混音。</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n功能与特性：</p>\r\n<p>-离散式A类电路设计</p>\r\n<p>-22段LED电平表</p>\r\n<p>-拐点调节旋钮</p>\r\n<p>-可选音色特性处理</p>\r\n<p>-可将8台TRAKKER连接进行环绕声混音 <br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'images/201210/1351554643080135696.jpg', 'images/201210/1351554643038811404.jpg', 'images/201210/1351554643949184658.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1351554643, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1351556087, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1179, 115, 'osc001179', 'osc1179', 'Crane Song Spider 8通道话筒放大器', '+', 120, 143, '', 0, 0.000, 84000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p>Spider是一款高质量的8通道话放/混音系统，并具备两种类型的数字输出：立体声及8通道输出。其中，立体声输出可为那些进行立体声及多轨录音的工程师们提供更为灵活且应用广泛的音频路由，而八通道输出则方便该系统作为数字音频工作站、数字调音台及数字录音机的模拟前端设备使用。</p>\r\n<p>Spider插入点的最大模拟电平可达+25dBm，且全部分立式A类话放及转换器模块都采用了高质量、低噪声的设计，可满足现场及录音室立体声录音、多轨录音和广播工程等应用需要。此外，Spider还可用作数字音频工作站前端设备、离线信号处理设备或立体声分组混音设备。</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n功能与特性：</p>\r\n<p>-6dB-66dB输入增益调节（6dB为调节单位）</p>\r\n<p>-通道电平控制</p>\r\n<p>-立体声输出母线声像控制</p>\r\n<p>-48v幻象供电开关</p>\r\n<p>-线路/话筒输入切换</p>\r\n<p>-反相开关</p>\r\n<p>-低切滤波器</p>\r\n<p>-立体声母线分配切换</p>\r\n<p>-Fat话放开关（可使声音更加饱满）</p>\r\n<p>-16段电平表（0读数表示模数转换削波失真）</p>\r\n<p>-话放部分削波指示灯</p>\r\n<p>-模数转换峰值限制器</p>\r\n<p>-通道插入点可用于话放增益信号直接输出</p>\r\n<p>-最高采样率支持192kHz</p>\r\n<p>-字时钟输入与输出</p>\r\n<p>-15bits-24bits抖动控制切换</p>\r\n<p>-DSP模拟磁带仿真效果（各通道调节）</p>\r\n<p>-数字输出（AES支持192kHz采样率，ADAT光纤支持96kHz采样率）<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'images/201210/1351555451898180668.jpg', 'images/201210/1351555451264726141.jpg', 'images/201210/1351555451246406770.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1351555451, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1351556138, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1180, 121, 'osc001180', 'osc1180', 'Crane Song STC-8立体声压缩器', '+', 109, 143, '', 0, 0.000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p>STC-8是一款高质量的压缩器，能够在不牺牲音乐品质及声音丰富谐波的前提下进行信号增益提升。它具有可靠的峰值限制器，可提供过载保护，因此对于数字录音及广播工程至关重要。此外，STC-8独特的设计使其不仅可以提供干净透明的信号增益控制，也能够模拟老式设备以创造与众不同的新声音&mdash;&mdash;这一切都是通过一个可切换的改进电路为声音加入模拟感和电子管的温暖感来实现的。用户可通过前面板的多种优化预置快速得到各具特色的声音，STEREOLINK开关还能实现独立单声道及立体声关联的切换控制。</p>\r\n<p>STC-8先进的旁链功能允许使用相同的增益控制电路同时进行压缩和峰值限制。分立式A类电路的设计还能确保极高的信号质量。</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n功能与特性：</p>\r\n<p>-压缩/限制同时处理</p>\r\n<p>-分立式A类电路</p>\r\n<p>-平衡式/无变压器输入输出</p>\r\n<p>-快速便捷的预置</p>\r\n<p>-创造特色的声音</p>\r\n<p>-高精度信号过载保护</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'images/201210/1351555885338957059.jpg', 'images/201210/1351555885315732384.jpg', 'images/201210/1351555885183253784.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1351555885, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1351556174, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1181, 151, 'osc001181', 'osc1181', 'Crane Song IBIS  母带处理EQ均衡器', '+', 87, 0, '', 0, 0.000, 47250, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">IBIS是一款模拟均衡器，采用独特的设计将均衡技术提升到了一个新的水平。四段调节模块可选择以某一固定音高为中心频点进行均衡调整，并覆盖了从32Hz&quot;C&quot;到22.35kHz&quot;F&quot;的音高范围，极大地方便了音乐家与工程师之间的技术交流。带宽设置范围可从0.2个倍频程到4个倍频程，提升/衰减范围为12dB。</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">低切滤波器可选择以20Hz至150Hz为频点，并进行每倍频程12dB或24dB的滚降衰减。同大多数CraneSong产品一样，IBIS也采用了分立式A类电路，且具备独特的可调式染色功能，可为全部通道或某一独立频段加入模拟温暖感。此外，IBIS还有一款增强的母带版本。</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">功能与特性：</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">分立式A类电路</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">-四段均衡调节</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">-以32Hz&quot;C&quot;到22.35kHz&quot;F&quot;的音高为中心调节频点</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">-0.2倍频程到4倍频程的带宽设置范围</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">-12dB提升/衰减范围</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">-20Hz到150Hz可选频点低切滤波器</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">-可调式染色功能&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span>&nbsp;</p>', 'images/201210/1351556531077365968.jpg', 'images/201210/1351556531693833968.jpg', 'images/201210/1351556531327899201.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1351556531, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1351556682, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1172, 49, 'osc001172', 'osc1172', 'ADAM Sub F有源监听音箱', '+', 122, 34, '', 0, 0.000, 3800, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p>ADAM Sub F音箱</p>\r\n<p>我们所有的超低音箱都致力于满足ADAM Audio最核心的目标：提供有可能的最真实的音乐。对于超低音箱来说，这意味着在保持功率足够，并且音质精准的同时，避免低频音量&ldquo;夸张&rdquo;，而损失声场的准确度。ADAM超低音箱的任务就是在低频以及最低频率范围内，保持ADAM惯有的清澈透明的音质。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sub F是一个很小，但是功率很足的超低音箱，内置强劲的8寸低音单元，1.5英寸音圈。它使用了150W（rms）的ICE Power的功放。这个功放在以最大功率输出的时候，温度仍然很低，就算持续工作也不例外。</p>\r\n<p>Sub F非常适合为F5以及F7提供更低更有力的低频信号。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>控制</p>\r\n<p>这个超低音箱后面板有数个可调参数：1个音量旋钮（-&infin;到+6 dB）、1个分频点控制器、以及1个相位控制器。</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>技术指标：</p>\r\n<p>&bull; 8寸碳布/纸复合低音单元</p>\r\n<p>&bull; 150W（ rms），200（mus ic）PWM功放</p>\r\n<p>&bull;自动待机</p>\r\n<p>&bull;增益、分频点、相位反转控制</p>\r\n<p>&bull; 32Hz - 50/150Hz</p>\r\n<p>&bull;输入接口：XLR复合大三芯接口+RCA接口</p>\r\n<p>&bull;输出接口：2个XLR（立体声）接口</p>\r\n<p>&bull;最大声压级111dB</p>\r\n<p>&bull; H x W x D: 350 x 250 x 341 mm</p>\r\n<p>&bull; 9.9 kg</p>\r\n<p>&bull;质保2年</p>', 'images/201207/1343287462159946049.jpg', 'images/201207/1343287462778906684.jpg', 'images/201207/1343287462364020817.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1343287462, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1343849972, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1203, 113, 'osc001203', 'osc1203', 'Mercury Brüder 定制版双通道话筒放大器', '+', 47, 144, '', 0, 0.000, 43940, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<h1>Br&uuml;der</h1>\r\n<h5>Studio Microphone Preamplifier</h5>\r\n<p>The Mercury Br&uuml;der combines one M72s channel and one M76m channel in a single 3U package. This unit is now available from our Custom Shop (special order).</p>\r\n<p>Both channels are multipurpose tools for making music.</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury M72s is warm and punchy, with a thick bottom end, a great push in the mid range and a open airy top end. The M72s performs great on vocals, bass, drums, acoustic and electric guitars, as well as room and overhead applications.</p>\r\n<p>The M76m is warm, open and airy. Compared to the M72s, the M76m is overall more evenly &quot;EQ''ed,&quot; meaning there is not a push in the low or mids. The M76m shines on vocals, bass and guitars (you have amazing control on the amplifier''s tone), and opens up your room and overhead mics. With 72dB (+/-) of total gain and a choice of high or low input impedance &mdash; ribbon mics are big and open with the M76m.</p>\r\n<p>The M72s has 58dB of gain and the M76m has about 72dB of gain (60dB input gain, +6dB(+/-) of level control and +6dB when low impedance is selected).</p>', 'images/201301/1359091657105844322.jpg', 'images/201301/1359091657816852120.jpg', 'images/201301/1359091657642255929.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1359091657, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1364327041, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1204, 113, 'osc001204', 'osc1204', 'Mercury M72s  CSV （Custom Shop Version）定制版双通道话筒放大器', '+', 49, 144, '', 0, 0.000, 36490, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<h1>M72s - Custom Shop Version</h1>\r\n<h5>Studio Microphone Amplifiers</h5>\r\n<p>In the mid-sixties, at Abbey Road Studios legends were born. Not just the Beatles or George Martin, but also the REDD.37 recording desk that was used to record most of their earlier work. The very rare amplifiers used in that desk were called &quot;V72s&quot; and were a modified version of the standard Telefunken / Siemens V72 module.</p>\r\n<p>The more common V72 amplifier modules were later modified and have been sold for many years as outboard preamplifiers all over the world. These V72 modules have not been available new for 40 years, and working units have become extremely rare and expensive. It is the uniquely musical tonal characteristics of these preamps have made them the prized possession of many engineers lucky enough to get the vintage modules, and a &quot;secret weapon&quot; for many studio musicians. With that in mind, Mercury Recording Equipment has made a faithful reproduction in the M72s -- not only of how the units behave, but of how they SOUND overall. The addition of pad, phase, phantom and gain controls make it even more versatile without sacrificing the most important feature: Musicality.</p>\r\n<p>The most sought after Telefunken/Siemens &quot;V series&quot; modules are famous for being used in Abbey Road''s REDD.37 consoles. These amplifiers were called &quot;V72s&quot; and were a modified version of the standard V72 modules that were much more common. Unlike those vintage modules that had fixed gain, The V72 at 34dB, and the &quot;V72s&quot; at 40dB, the Mercury M72s has variable mic gain from 28dB to 58dB. Also, with the M72s, you have a selectable input pad of -16dB or -28dB for even more control. When the -28dB pad is engaged and it is set at the lowest gain setting (28dB) you can run line level signal through the M72s. This will provide a warm, rich path for mixes, keyboards, drum machines, samples etc... There are also all the modern features we expect on a new piece of equipment: 48V DC (Phantom), Phase Reverse (Polarity) and Direct Input for Bass or Electric Guitar per channel. The Mercury M72s has the rich lows and punchy mids that the vintage V72 modules have but a more open high end. The Mercury M72s Studio Microphone Amplifier has that &quot;vintage&quot; tone and &quot;break up&quot; like the original modules but it is a bit more musical over all (not cleaner... more musical, there is a huge difference).</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury M72s brings that &quot;vintage&quot; magic back! It is truly a new classic for today as well as for the next 50 years!<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>MERCURY RECORDING EQUIPMENT has gone to great lengths to recreate the pride and passion of the past, both sonically and aesthetically, while offering the reliability of a present day production. The choices made in looks, layout, functionality, features and build quality all answer back to one question: How would &quot;they&quot; have done it today?</p>\r\n<p>Mercury Recording Equipment Co. products are hand wired and/or assembled using silver solder and no-compromise parts. All Mercury products are transformer balanced, inputs and outputs and there are no I.C.s (chips) in the signal path. The chassis and front panels have a very distinctive &quot;vintage&quot; look with custom powder coating finish. They look as good as they sound!</p>', 'images/201301/1359091927507591636.jpg', 'images/201301/1359091927322835263.jpg', 'images/201301/1359091927287801221.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1359091927, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1364326943, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1205, 113, 'osc001205', 'osc1205', 'Mercury M76m  CSV(Custom Shop Version) 定制版双通道话筒放大器', '+', 47, 144, '', 0, 0.000, 48940, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<h1>M76m - Custom Shop Version</h1>\r\n<h5>Studio Microphone Amplifier</h5>\r\n<p>First, Mercury Recording Equipment Co. successfully recreated the original V72s with the highly regarded Mercury M72s. Now, with the Mercury M76m, we have brought to life the V72s'' &quot;big brother&quot; - the V76. The Mercury M76m is a recreation of the original German designed Telefunken / Siemens amplifier module used in many European broadcast and recording desks. The V76 modules, however, are more well known as an outboard rack mounted preamp and are highly sought after by studios and engineers all over the world. Of all the V76 amplifiers, the &quot;V76m&quot; has always been the most desired because of its useful variable gain control, (as well as no filters intended for broadcast use). Original V76 modules have not been available new for 40 years and working vintage units have become extremely rare and expensive. Furthermore, due to its overly compact modular design, the V76 modules are now, after four decades, not as mechanically sound as they once were which causes problems sonically.</p>\r\n<p>With that in mind, Mercury Recording Equipment Co. has recreated the transformer balanced, four tube per channel, high gain amplifier. Keeping the integrity of the original circuit, the M76m has open, warm tonality. After many years in development, Mercury has now built what is quite possibly the ultimate combination of vintage sound and modern features.</p>\r\n<p>We made it first priority to build a modern Studio Microphone Amplifier that sounds identical to the original. Which was successful, by drawing on years of experience, repairing, rebuilding, and most importantly listening to the Telefunken / Siemens V76 modules. We did not stop there, however. Mercury took it one step farther than a &quot;recreation&quot;. Using our years of professional service and taking note of what modifications and features the professional recording engineers wished their original V76 modules had Mercury added a few new features that the original studio microphone amplifiers and even the best &quot;vintage&quot; reracks never had.</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury M76m has an Impedance Select switch for both high and low impedance devices. Secondly, a Level Control (which will work as a fader as well as add another 6dB (+ / -) from the second stage amplifier) and a Output Attenuation control (-0 to -10dB) has been added for even more control, including the ability to overdrive the amplifier in several different ways, if desired. The Gain control is 0 to +60dB in 6dB increments, that works in conjunction with the Level control and Output Attenuation Control. Also, all the staple features one expects from a modern piece of equipment were added: Phantom power, Phase Reversal (Polarity) , and an amazing sounding direct input on each channel. The M76m is truly a new classic for today as well as the benchmark in Studio Microphone Amplifiers for the next 50 years!</p>', 'images/201301/1359092156849377919.jpg', 'images/201301/1359092156116621300.jpg', 'images/201301/1359092156373529217.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1359092156, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1364326922, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1206, 151, 'osc001206', 'osc1206', 'Mercury EQ-H2 定制版双通道均衡器', '+', 52, 144, '', 0, 0.000, 37490, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<h1>EQ-H2</h1>\r\n<h5>Dual Channel Studio Program Equalizer</h5>\r\n<p>The Mercury EQ-H1, EQ-P1, EQ-H2 and EQ-P2 are all based on the original Pultec equalizers which were tools developed to deal with the limitations of recorded music. Limitations that most often manifest themselves in the highest and lowest frequencies of the program material. The Mercury Studio Program Equalizers, like the family of original Pultec EQs, are originally designed to bring back the life and musicality lost in a recording. Whether by accident or genius, nothing has been able to do this better in music production than a passive equalizer with tube gain make up amplifier (&lsquo;Pultec style&rsquo;) equalizer. The interaction of the passive boosting and attenuating shelving EQs (not relying on negative feedback), as well as the transformers, tubes and other amplification circuitry all add to the incredibly musical character of the product. Working engineers try other types of equalizers, but always end up coming back to the Pultec style as the equalizer of choice for those final touches while tracking or mixing and even mastering at times.</p>\r\n<p>Now in this modern age of digital recording, where the source you put into the DAW is exactly what you have on the track, with no rounded edges, no slight compression and none of the &ldquo;pixie dust&rdquo; that came with analog tape, the Mercury family of equalizers are needed more than ever to help add the musicality, warmth and tone to your tracks that we have all treasured.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Frequencies</strong><br />\r\n&bull;Low Frequency Select (CPS; Cycles per second): 20, 30, 60, 100, 200 Hz<br />\r\n&bull;Low Frequency Boost Control: Shelf Boost, 0dB to +13dB<br />\r\n&bull;Low Frequency Attenuate Control: Shelf Atten. 0dB to -17dB<br />\r\n&bull;High Frequency Select (KCS; kilocycles per second ): 3, 4, 5, 8, 10, 12, 16 kHz<br />\r\n&bull;High Frequency Boost Control: Shelf Boost, 0dB to +16dB<br />\r\n&bull;High Frequency Attenuate Control: 10k Shelf Attenuate, 0dB to -16dB</p>\r\n<!--p>xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx xx x xx xxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxxxx x x x xxxxxxx xxxxxxx xxxxxxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxxx xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxx xxxxxxx xx xxxxx xxxxxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxxx xx xxxxxx xxxxxxxx xxxxxxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxx x xxxxx xxxxxxxx</p-->', 'images/201301/1359092450813836321.jpg', 'images/201301/1359092450589189619.jpg', 'images/201301/1359092450680698130.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1359092450, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1364326738, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1207, 151, 'osc001207', 'osc1207', 'Mercury EQ-P2  定制版双通道均衡器', '+', 50, 144, '', 0, 0.000, 42940, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<h1>EQ-P2</h1>\r\n<h5>Dual Channel Studio Program Equalizer</h5>\r\n<p>The Mercury EQ-H1, EQ-P1, EQ-H2 and EQ-P2 are all based on the original Pultec equalizers which were tools developed to deal with the limitations of recorded music. Limitations that most often manifest themselves in the highest and lowest frequencies of the program material. The Mercury Studio Program Equalizers, like the family of original Pultec EQs, are originally designed to bring back the life and musicality lost in a recording. Whether by accident or genius, nothing has been able to do this better in music production than a passive equalizer with tube gain make up amplifier (&lsquo;Pultec style&rsquo;) equalizer. The interaction of the passive boosting and attenuating shelving EQs (not relying on negative feedback), as well as the transformers, tubes and other amplification circuitry all add to the incredibly musical character of the product. Working engineers try other types of equalizers, but always end up coming back to the Pultec style as the equalizer of choice for those final touches while tracking or mixing and even mastering at times.</p>\r\n<p>Now in this modern age of digital recording, where the source you put into the DAW is exactly what you have on the track, with no rounded edges, no slight compression and none of the &ldquo;pixie dust&rdquo; that came with analog tape, the Mercury family of equalizers are needed more than ever to help add the musicality, warmth and tone to your tracks that we have all treasured.</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Frequencies</strong><br />\r\nLow Frequency Select (CPS; Cycles per second): 20, 30, 60, 100, 200 Hz <br />\r\nLow Frequency Boost Control: Shelf Boost, 0dB to +13dB <br />\r\nLow Frequency Attenuate Control: Shelf Atten. 0dB to -17dB <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Select (KCS; kilocycles per second ): 3, 4, 5, 8, 10, 12, 16 kHz <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Boost Control: Shelf Boost, 0dB to +16dB <br />\r\nHigh Frequency Attenuate Control: 10k Shelf Attenuate, 0dB to -16dB</p>', 'images/201301/1359092632111234708.jpg', 'images/201301/1359092632249051345.jpg', 'images/201301/1359092632397815842.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1359092632, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1363135590, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1208, 113, 'osc001208', 'osc1208', 'Mercury AM16 双通道晶体管话筒放器', '+', 47, 144, '', 0, 0.000, 19490, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<h1>AM16</h1>\r\n<h5>Transistor Type Microphone Amplifiers</h5>\r\n<p>The Mercury AM16 is a 19&quot; rack mountable version of the original American, modular, transistor type preamplifier built in the 1960''s. The AM16 is well known for being over all very musical, open and airy on the top end and having a tube-like &quot;air&quot; characteristic not found in most amplifiers of the same type. The Mercury AM16 is available in both two channel and one channel (AM16/1) versions. Features include: Input Pad (-24dB) as well as a Adjustable Input (Pad) Attenuator (-0, -6, -12, -18 and -24dB), Phantom (48V), Phase Reverse (Polarity), an Output Control (Fader) and a newly designed FET Direct Input, per channel. The Mercury AM16''s internally mounted power supply uses a toroidal transformer and is regulated for super low noise and stable performance. In addition each amplifier channel is locally regulated to eliminate cross talk between channels. The Mercury AM16 is housed in a beautiful, gray hammer finish, steel chassis and the aluminum front (control) panel has a custom powder coated finish giving the Mercury AM16 the look and feel of the &quot;vintage&quot; original.</p>\r\n<p><img alt="" width="400" height="75" src="/images/upload/Image/mercury_am162_back_med.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p>The inputs and outputs of the Mercury AM16 are coupled through custom wound transformers that are modeled after the originals . The Amplifier gain is set at 50dB like the original &quot;R&quot; high gain setting. We have also added features that make the Mercury AM16 more flexible than the original or even a modern rack solution.</p>\r\n<p>We have worked with many of the vintage AM16 modules. At Marquette Audio Labs we have been racking and modiifing modules since 1994 and the AM16 has always been a personal favorite. We have always had continuous great feedback from clients about the musical characteristics of the AM16. But the original modules have not been made for some 30+ years and supply is not able to meet demand. The Mercury AM16 solves that problem with the same fully discrete, &quot;transistor type&quot; circuitry and more importantly the same musical quality and performance of the original modules.</p>\r\n<p>The Original AM16 Amplifier Literature stated: &quot;The AM16 is primarily a microphone pre-mixing amplifier (mic pre). However, its performance also qualifies it for use as a post-mixing (booster) and as a low-level program amplifier. Of special note is the low noise generation figure.&quot; Mercury recording Equipment has achieved it goal with the Mercury AM16. This goal was to make it possible to use the amplifier to its original, full potential. The Mercury AM16 can be used as a microphone amplifier (mic pre) and you can also use it as a line amplifier (booster) by using the combination of the -24dB pad and the Input Attenuator (Pad) and Output Fader control. This gives you the option to run your mixes through the Mercury AM16 or use for additional (musical) gain on another device, when needed. Thirdly, you have the option of the Direct Input on the Mercury AM16, which was added for uses for direct recording of Bass and Electric guitar as well as keyboards and drum machines etc... The FET Direct Input on the Mercury AM16 is very full sounding. There is more mid range and low end presence than most D.I.s as well as an open and airy top end that the AM16 is famous for.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'images/201301/1359092964606775442.jpg', 'images/201301/1359092964720527869.jpg', 'images/201301/1359092964640476278.jpg', 1, '', 0, 1, 0, 1359092964, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1364324520, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1212, 132, 'osc001212', 'osc1212', 'Bricasti M7 Reverb Processor', '+', 15, 145, '', 0, 0.000, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p>The Bricasti Design Model 7 provides the highest level of musicality and ease of control imaginable in a processor dedicated to the task of reverberation. A modern high resolution digital design, utilizing a stunning array of the latest DSP processors, provides a platform for the long overdue next step in reverb processing algorithms. A separate fully differential analog section and dedicated transformer based linear power supply provide the finest analog specifications of any product of it''s kind. An exceptionally strong stainless steel chassis, and a tooled aluminum front panel, combine with a classic high visibility display and straight forward human interface, to complete an enduring design that is intended to fulfill its role, now and into the future. Each design element of the Model 7 is a carefully considered statement of our vision of what the evolution of reverberation processing in its most classic form can be. With a deep appreciation of the best designs which precede it, and a passion for moving the science of reverberation forward, the Model 7 provides a palette of sounds that encompass the familiar as well as new expressions in the art. Listen to the new reference in reverb processing; it will bring new life to your art, in a way unimagined by any process before it.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>一直以来，好的单机版硬件混响效果器，表现总是比最好的插件优异，然而，这个领域的选择总因着数位设备很高的研发费用，而难免受限于少数几个厂牌与型号。</p>\r\n<p>Lexicon 224''s, 224XL''s以及480L''s至今仍很热卖，这些经典机种其绵密与具有包覆感的声音特性，至今仍无法取代！新的机种像是TC M4000以及System 6000或是Lexicon 960，受人喜爱也相对的安静，但残响总让人感觉是浮在讯号的顶端而并不是变成讯号的一部分。对于各种不同的应用场合来说，这些机器通常表现很优异，但对于某些特定场合来说就暴露了其缺点，特别是对于直接收录的鼓以及人声。</p>\r\n<p>Bricasti是一个新的公司，这名字对于某些人来说也一定很陌生，不过他的血统却很纯正，这个公司最早是起源于负责设计Lexicon经典效果器的团队，著名的480L也是出自他们之手，他们现今的设计仍然强烈保留住当年的个性，但具备数位的输入以及输出端子，以及更友善的人机介面。</p>\r\n<p>Bricasti M7因其源于经典Lexicon的血统，在这一台流线型的1U机身当中，具备令人怀念的丰富且深沉的残响，它编辑的功能很广泛，但具有逻辑且操作简单，而工厂的预设值涵盖了许多组非常实用的效果。当年的Lexicon 480L设计师很自豪的说：&ldquo;Bricasti M7不只是来简单模拟或者替代Lexicon 480L，它有自己的声音&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>我们将这机器与Lexicons - PCM91以及经典的224(Lexicon最有名的残响之一)比较，虽然某些虽然有些原厂预设像是PCM91的重组，但Bricasti的声音却更为丰富，具备许多现代残响的包覆感。很明显的，残响的尾巴更平滑自然，并且没有91系列&ldquo;吱吱&rdquo;的高频声，表示它的处理能力更上一层楼。当我们用 M7和Lex 224对比，它的表现更为耀眼，许多基本的预设值都不容易辨识，但两者都具备丰富且深沉的声音特性，不过Bricasti更安静，要说到编辑的能力那就根本无从比较，M7在各方面都胜出，从各种数位输入到广大的内建预设以及编辑所有参数的能力都是。</p>\r\n<p>很少有制造商会对新的机种自我宣扬，但Bricasti M7确实如此。它是一台优秀的机器，并且很快就会在发烧音乐；后期制作以及广告录音室等许多不同场合中被广泛使用，如果你打算购买一台高品质的残响，并且只打算买一台，那么Bricasti M7绝对是首选，因为它具有杰出的音质和相对友善的价格。</p>\r\n<p><strong>预设效果特性介绍</strong></p>\r\n<p>&bull;100组独家的预设效果 <br />\r\n&bull;革命性的新残响演算法：True Stereo Reverb Process <br />\r\n&bull;经典与创新的预设效果; Halls, Plates, Rooms, Chambers, Ambient Spaces <br />\r\n&bull;每组效果具备12组预设可调参数 <br />\r\n&bull;100组使用者设定效果 <br />\r\n&bull;4组面板可自行设定的&ldquo;Favorites&rdquo;的最常使用效果，可快 <br />\r\n&bull;比较以及切换<br />\r\n硬体设计特性</p>\r\n<p>&bull;双独立电源供应 <br />\r\n&bull;专为类比电路设计的独立环形变压器 <br />\r\n&bull;专位数位电路设计的高表现切换式变压器 <br />\r\n&bull;数位与类比模组分离 <br />\r\n&bull;抗腐蚀不锈钢外壳 <br />\r\n&bull;面板、旋钮以及按键采电镀铝壳处理 <br />\r\n&bull;Postive feel 2 db拨段式类比输入控制 <br />\r\n&bull;MIDI I/O <br />\r\n&bull;美国手工制造</p>\r\n<p>*上述文字部分描述摘自midifan网站</p>', 'images/201303/1364176140546793436.jpg', 'images/201303/1364176140773984706.jpg', 'images/201303/1364176139770088269.jpg', 1, '', 1, 1, 0, 1364175471, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1364240185, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1209, 112, 'osc001209', 'osc1209', 'Mercury AM16-1 单通道晶体管话筒放器', '+', 45, 144, '', 0, 0.000, 10950, 1, 0, 1, 1, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p>Single channel version of the AM16 Transistor Type Microphone Preamplifier.</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury AM16 is a 19&quot; rack mountable version of the original American, modular, transistor type preamplifier built in the 1960''s. The AM16 is well known for being over all very musical, open and airy on the top end and having a tube-like &quot;air&quot; characteristic not found in most amplifiers of the same type. The Mercury AM16 is available in both two channel and one channel (AM16/1) versions. Features include: Input Pad (-24dB) as well as a Adjustable Input (Pad) Attenuator (-0, -6, -12, -18 and -24dB), Phantom (48V), Phase Reverse (Polarity), an Output Control (Fader) and a newly designed FET Direct Input, per channel. The Mercury AM16''s internally mounted power supply uses a toroidal transformer and is regulated for super low noise and stable performance. In addition each amplifier channel is locally regulated to eliminate cross talk between channels. The Mercury AM16 is housed in a beautiful, gray hammer finish, steel chassis and the aluminum front (control) panel has a custom powder coated finish giving the Mercury AM16 the look and feel of the &quot;vintage&quot; original.</p>\r\n<p>The inputs and outputs of the Mercury AM16 are coupled through custom wound transformers that are modeled after the originals . The Amplifier gain is set at 50dB like the original &quot;R&quot; high gain setting. We have also added features that make the Mercury AM16 more flexible than the original or even a modern rack solution.</p>\r\n<p>We have worked with many of the vintage AM16 modules. At Marquette Audio Labs we have been racking and modiifing modules since 1994 and the AM16 has always been a personal favorite. We have always had continuous great feedback from clients about the musical characteristics of the AM16. But the original modules have not been made for some 30+ years and supply is not able to meet demand. The Mercury AM16 solves that problem with the same fully discrete, &quot;transistor type&quot; circuitry and more importantly the same musical quality and performance of the original modules.</p>\r\n<p>The Original AM16 Amplifier Literature stated: &quot;The AM16 is primarily a microphone pre-mixing amplifier (mic pre). However, its performance also qualifies it for use as a post-mixing (booster) and as a low-level program amplifier. Of special note is the low noise generation figure.&quot; Mercury recording Equipment has achieved it goal with the Mercury AM16. This goal was to make it possible to use the amplifier to its original, full potential. The Mercury AM16 can be used as a microphone amplifier (mic pre) and you can also use it as a line amplifier (booster) by using the combination of the -24dB pad and the Input Attenuator (Pad) and Output Fader control. This gives you the option to run your mixes through the Mercury AM16 or use for additional (musical) gain on another device, when needed. Thirdly, you have the option of the Direct Input on the Mercury AM16, which was added for uses for direct recording of Bass and Electric guitar as well as keyboards and drum machines etc... The FET Direct Input on the Mercury AM16 is very full sounding. There is more mid range and low end presence than most D.I.s as well as an open and airy top end that the AM16 is famous for.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'images/201301/1359093151578070894.jpg', 'images/201301/1359093151553767158.jpg', 'images/201301/1359093151211553754.jpg', 1, '', 0, 1, 0, 1359093151, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1364324301, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1210, 113, 'osc001210', 'osc1210', 'Mercury Grand Pre 双通道话筒放大器', '+', 46, 144, '', 0, 0.000, 19940, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<h1>Grand Pre</h1>\r\n<h5>Solid State Microphone Amplifiers</h5>\r\n<p>The Mercury Grand Pre is more open and musical than other similar amplifiers of the same type and/or topology. Just to be perfectly clear... the Mercury Grand Pre is not another &quot;Twelve Seventy Two&quot; clone. Instead, the Grand Pre is the new, Alternative British Classic!</p>\r\n<p><img width="400" height="74" alt="" src="/images/upload/Image/mercury_gp2_back_med.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p>The Mercury Grand Pre is available in both two channel and one channel (GP/1) versions. Features include: Input Gain Control 0-60dB in 12dB steps (-0, -12, -24, -36, -48 and -60dB), that works in combination with the Fine Gain Control (trim) that is +/- 8dB. Phantom (48V), Phase Reverse (Polarity), an Output Control (Fader) and a newly designed FET Direct Input, per channel. The FET Direct Input on the Mercury Grand Pre is very full sounding. There is more mid range and low end presence then most D.I.s as well as an open and airy top end and overall punchiness you would expect from a Class A Discrete Amplifier. The inputs and outputs of the Grand Pre are balanced using the original Sowter transformers. The Mercury Grand Pre''s internally mounted power supply uses a toroidal transformer and is regulated for super low noise and stable performance. In addition each amplifier channel is locally regulated to eliminate cross talk between channels.</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury Grand Pre is 19&quot; rack mountable and housed in a beautiful, gray hammer finish, steel chassis. The aluminum front (control) panel has a custom powder coated finish giving the Mercury Grand Pre the look and feel of the era it comes from with a twist. The Grand Pre has the &quot;look&quot; of a Classic Hot rod with it''s black, red and chrome color scheme. The Mercury Grand Pre has &quot;the goods&quot; under the hood and is always ready to race for pink slips. Compare it to other mic pres of the same type and you will understand why it is called the &quot;Grand Pre&quot; and why it holds the checkered flag!</p>', 'images/201301/1359093342536203031.jpg', 'images/201301/1359093342216164993.jpg', 'images/201301/1359093342199905064.jpg', 1, '', 0, 1, 0, 1359093342, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1364324575, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO `sm_goods` VALUES(1211, 112, 'osc001211', 'osc1211', 'Mercury Grand Pre-1 单通道话筒放大器', '+', 44, 144, '', 0, 0.000, 10950, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0.00, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '<p>Single channel version of the Grand Pre Solid State Microphone Preamplifier.</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury Grand Pre is more open and musical than other similar amplifiers of the same type and/or topology. Just to be perfectly clear... the Mercury Grand Pre is not another &quot;Twelve Seventy Two&quot; clone. Instead, the Grand Pre is the new, Alternative British Classic!</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\nThe Mercury Grand Pre is available in both two channel and one channel (GP/1) versions. Features include: Input Gain Control 0-60dB in 12dB steps (-0, -12, -24, -36, -48 and -60dB), that works in combination with the Fine Gain Control (trim) that is +/- 8dB. Phantom (48V), Phase Reverse (Polarity), an Output Control (Fader) and a newly designed FET Direct Input, per channel. The FET Direct Input on the Mercury Grand Pre is very full sounding. There is more mid range and low end presence then most D.I.s as well as an open and airy top end and overall punchiness you would expect from a Class A Discrete Amplifier. The inputs and outputs of the Grand Pre are balanced using the original Sowter transformers. The Mercury Grand Pre''s internally mounted power supply uses a toroidal transformer and is regulated for super low noise and stable performance. In addition each amplifier channel is locally regulated to eliminate cross talk between channels.</p>\r\n<p>The Mercury Grand Pre is 19&quot; rack mountable and housed in a beautiful, gray hammer finish, steel chassis. The aluminum front (control) panel has a custom powder coated finish giving the Mercury Grand Pre the look and feel of the era it comes from with a twist. The Grand Pre has the &quot;look&quot; of a Classic Hot rod with it''s black, red and chrome color scheme. The Mercury Grand Pre has &quot;the goods&quot; under the hood and is always ready to race for pink slips. Compare it to other mic pres of the same type and you will understand why it is called the &quot;Grand Pre&quot; and why it holds the checkered flag!<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'images/201301/1359093588791447530.jpg', 'images/201301/1359093588783854604.jpg', 'images/201301/1359093588292980319.jpg', 1, '', 0, 1, 0, 1359093588, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1364324611, 1, '', -1, '', '', 0, 0, '');
